    "title": "Avoid CUDA context initialization at import time",
    "user": {
      "login": "henrylhtsang",
      "id": 91030427,
      "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjkxMDMwNDI3",
      "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/91030427?v=4",
      "gravatar_id": "",
      "url": "https://api.github.com/users/henrylhtsang",
      "html_url": "https://github.com/henrylhtsang",
      "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/henrylhtsang/followers",
      "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/henrylhtsang/following{/other_user}",
      "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/henrylhtsang/gists{/gist_id}",
      "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/henrylhtsang/starred{/owner}{/repo}",
      "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/henrylhtsang/subscriptions",
      "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/henrylhtsang/orgs",
      "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/henrylhtsang/repos",
      "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/henrylhtsang/events{/privacy}",
      "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/henrylhtsang/received_events",
      "type": "User",
      "user_view_type": "public",
      "site_admin": false
    },
    "body": "Previously, `import quack.gemm_interface` called\r\n`get_device_capacity(torch.device(\"cuda\"))` at module level to determine which autotuning configs to generate. This eagerly initialized a CUDA context. In our use case, sometimes we do it in a CPU only environment. \r\n\r\nFix: generate configs for all supported arches (sm90 + sm100) at import time — this is pure CPU work. Tag each GemmConfig with its target `device_capacity` and filter to the actual device at runtime in `prune_invalid_gemm_configs`, which already runs at call time when the tensor's device is known.\r\n\r\ncc @thakkarV ",
    "created_at": "2026-03-17T21:15:29Z",
    "updated_at": "2026-03-18T18:44:41Z",
    "closed_at": "2026-03-18T18:44:41Z",
    "merged_at": "2026-03-18T18:44:41Z",
